'''Automatic sealup''' was a safety feature on [[Starship/Legends|spacecraft]] and [[Space station/Legends|space stations]] triggered when pressure sensors detected a sudden decompression or exposure to [[Vacuum/Legends|vacuum]]. An alarm signal would be instantly transmitted to a central station which would in turn immediately send commands closing all airtight bulkhead doors.

